<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4d075294-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443"><num value="12443">§ 12443.</num><heading> Eligible entities</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Entities eligible for grants under this part include—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d075295-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> jurisdictions or agencies within jurisdictions having authority or responsibility for developing or maintaining public databases, registries or victim notification systems;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d075296-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> nonprofit nongovernmental victim advocacy organizations having expertise regarding confidentiality, privacy, and information technology and how these issues are likely to impact the safety of victims;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d075297-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> States or State agencies;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d075298-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> local governments or agencies;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d075299-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> Indian tribal governments or tribal organizations;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d07529a-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> territorial governments, agencies, or organizations; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d07529b-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12443/7"><num value="7">(7)</num><content> nonprofit nongovernmental victim advocacy organizations, including statewide domestic violence and sexual assault coalitions.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id4d07529c-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tIV/s41103">Pub. L. 103–322, title IV, § 41103</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/109/162/tI/s107">Pub. L. 109–162, title I, § 107</ref>, <date date="2006-01-05">Jan. 5, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/2983">119 Stat. 2983</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
